1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:11,967
<i> Where were we again?</i>

2
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:14,567
<i>Oh yeah, you're going
to say goodbye now.</i>

3
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:20,233
<i> What's the news?</i>

4
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:21,300
<i> Sir, Markus is gone.</i>

5
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,133
<i> He took the bait.</i>

6
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:23,433
<i>We'll track the motorcycle now.</i>

7
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:25,333
<i> Where's Roman? Call him!</i>

8
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,033
<i>What are you doing here?
How did you escape?</i>

9
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:28,267
<i> You're an animal, Roman.</i>

10
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,100
<i>If you think your plan is right,
you should do it.</i>

11
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,400
<i> You should go to jail!</i>

12
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:34,833
<i> You were followed.</i>

13
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:36,100
<i> Put this in your brain.</i>

14
00:00:36,233 --> 00:00:37,967
<i>It's better that boss owes you
a debt of gratitude</i>

15
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:38,900
<i> than the other way around.</i>

16
00:00:39,033 --> 00:00:40,567
<i> So think about it.</i>

17
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:41,700
<i> Bok...</i>

18
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:45,167
<i>this is the solid evidence
we have.</i>

19
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,900
<i>Even if you didn't catch Roman,
it's still mission accomplished.</i>

20
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:50,067
<i>And with the help
of Markus' testimony,</i>

21
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,300
<i>I'm sure Victor Santiago will be
held accountable by the law.</i>

22
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:55,700
<i> How was your operation?</i>

23
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:56,767
<i> Is there any news yet?</i>

24
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,967
<i>Have you got solid evidence
against Amo?</i>

25
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:00,867
<i> Yes.</i>

26
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,333
<i>So, does that mean
we can put Amo in jail now?</i>

27
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,833
We're almost there, Lara.

28
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,200
Just a little bit more.

29
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:22,367
For the first time
in the history of Calabari,

30
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:25,467
the winning mayor and vice mayor
are a father and son tandem.

31
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,467
It's re-elected Mayor
Joaquin Guerrero

32
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,800
and former Councilor
Glen Guerrero.

33
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,500
After a peaceful election,

34
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,567
the Guerrero father and son
tandem finally won

35
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:36,333
the support of the people,

36
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,867
who said they believed
in their desire

37
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,400
to continue the city's reforms.

38
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:44,400
This is Mira Torres,
reporting for Today News.

39
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:49,633
It's a good day for Calabari!

40
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:52,400
You know, just because
your bet won,

41
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,433
you have the guts to say
that "It's a good day."

42
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:55,600
You're so noisy!

43
00:02:56,733 --> 00:02:58,600
Hey, what are you doing here?

44
00:02:58,733 --> 00:02:59,800
Don't you have a job to do?

45
00:03:00,967 --> 00:03:02,233
Hey, you should patrol
the streets.

46
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:03,967
We're paying you!

47
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,033
You're just standing here!

48
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:07,500
You're getting paid...

49
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:08,533
- Hey, you! What?
- Why?

50
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:10,767
Are you the captain now?
You're acting like it.

51
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,567
Get out.

52
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:13,000
Let's go, Abdul.

53
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:14,567
We're only pretending
to be like you, Captain.

54
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,567
Get to work!

55
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:23,067
El hepe! El hepe!

56
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:42,467
Vice Mayor Glen Guerrero.

57
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:46,267
It's soothing to the ears.

58
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,500
So nice to hear.

59
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:50,500
Boss,

60
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:53,300
even though I know this is just
the first step of your plans,

61
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,500
congratulations.

62
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:00,533
Thank you, Roman.

63
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:01,967
One by one.

64
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,300
Now that I'm seated in power,
we don't need to rush.

65
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,567
We don't need to rush.

66
00:04:12,267 --> 00:04:15,267
So, what's our next step?

67
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,200
You know me, Boss,
I don't like being bored.

68
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:20,333
I always want to be on the move.

69
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,033
Get rid of Markus.

70
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:26,800
You know, Boss, if there's
anyone who's going to screw you,

71
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:27,967
it's Markus.

72
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:29,600
You made a good decision.

73
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:33,000
He's already giving me a lot
of headaches.

74
00:04:45,867 --> 00:04:47,967
- Sir, what's my case?
- Go ahead.

75
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:53,167
- Sir, wait a minute. Wait, Sir.
- Go ahead.

76
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,800
Do you know I can sue you?

77
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:56,400
Sir, what's wrong with this?

78
00:04:56,933 --> 00:04:58,567
He's so drunk and causing
too much trouble.

79
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,833
- Let him spend the night there.
- I didn't drink too much.

80
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,200
- Okay, Sir.
- I'm just having fun, Sir.

81
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:08,400
Go ahead, come inside.

82
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:09,267
What's this, Sir?

83
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,500
Come on. Come in.

84
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:12,333
You're drinking, and you can't
even handle it.

85
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,633
Go ahead, come in.

86
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:16,433
You talk too much.

87
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:19,467
Noble.

88
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,633
Sir?

89
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:22,367
Can you buy some snacks first?
I'm a little hungry.

90
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:23,233
Your treat?

91
00:05:23,367 --> 00:05:24,633
- Of course.
- Yes.

92
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:25,633
Go ahead, I'll take care
of this.

93
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:27,467
Thank you, Sir. I can buy
a lot with this.

94
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:56,667
Boss...

95
00:05:57,967 --> 00:05:59,267
raise my salary, okay?

96
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:00,933
I'll take care of you.

97
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,967
Go ahead, finish him off.

98
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,800
I'm just drinking...

99
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,800
and you disturbed me.

100
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:22,133
I just want to have a good time.

101
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,367
Boss!

102
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:06,333
Boss!

103
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,400
What happened here?

104
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,267
- What did you do?
- Boss, wait.

105
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:18,133
What happened here?

106
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:21,400
He killed Markus and was
planning to kill the others too.

107
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,900
That's why I had to shoot him.

108
00:07:23,367 --> 00:07:24,033
Right?

109
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:26,367
- Yes, Sir.
- Yes, Sir.

110
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,833
Go ahead, call an ambulance.

111
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:29,167
- Hurry!
- Okay, Sir.

112
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:39,033
Don't you dare tell anyone
about this.

113
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:55,400
It's done, Boss.

114
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:56,633
Clean?

115
00:07:57,933 --> 00:07:59,667
I want this closed.

116
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:03,200
Clean, Boss,
just as you planned it.

117
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,467
It was just an accident.

118
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:07,333
Our guy inside said that...

119
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:12,500
when he shot the guy
we ordered to kill Markus,

120
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:15,867
there wasn't even an
investigation at the station.

121
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,967
It was clearly visible on CCTV.

122
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:22,167
Our guy went on a rampage,
got shot, and died.

123
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:23,233
It's done, Boss.

124
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:24,167
Clean.

125
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:26,367
Very good.

126
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:31,067
I'm going to start ruling
here in Calabari.

127
00:08:34,767 --> 00:08:36,300
Bobby, where are we going?

128
00:08:37,533 --> 00:08:39,733
This is where Godmother Dina
and I go before.

129
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:42,867
That's why I come here
when I miss her.

130
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,000
Come on. Sit down, sit down.

131
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:55,900
- Reign, I'm really sorry...
- Bobby...

132
00:08:57,867 --> 00:08:59,400
you have nothing
to apologize for...

133
00:09:00,567 --> 00:09:02,167
because it's not your fault.

134
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:06,667
I'm the one who has a lot
to apologize for...

135
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,133
because I fought you.

136
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,333
Despite everything I did
to you...

137
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:19,167
you still saved me.

138
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,900
So thank you very much, Bobby.

139
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:29,033
Reign, I can't forgive myself
if something bad happens to you.

140
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:35,767
Stop it, Bobby.
We're full of drama.

141
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:39,033
- Let's go buy some food.
- Come on, let's order.

142
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,067
Sir?

143
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,700
Yes, Ma'am?

144
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:41,900
What's that?

145
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,300
What do you've got there?

146
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:46,800
Ma'am, we have tofu,
fried fish...

147
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,300
Hello, Sir?

148
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:04,100
What?

149
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,333
Markus was killed?

150
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:13,167
Okay, Sir, I'll be there soon.

151
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:22,600
Reign, wait a minute, okay?

152
00:10:24,367 --> 00:10:25,567
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

153
00:10:27,367 --> 00:10:28,267
Hello, Enriquez?

154
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:30,733
Chief called.

155
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:33,000
It's Markus...

156
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,600
he was killed last night.

157
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,167
What?

158
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,733
Dad...

159
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,100
don't drink too much coffee.
Isn't it forbidden for you?

160
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:54,833
This is just my first cup.
It's not even finished yet.

161
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:57,667
Dad, you have to take care
of your body.

162
00:10:57,933 --> 00:10:59,600
Our fight is still a long one.

163
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:01,267
Okay, okay, fine.

164
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:03,233
Take this.

165
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,467
Here's your maintenance.

166
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:11,633
Thank you, Glen.

167
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:14,933
I'm proud of you.

168
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:18,633
You're my partner in taking care
of Calabari.

169
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:22,500
Thank you, Dad.

170
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,433
But you know...

171
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:28,933
I couldn't have done all this
if it weren't for you.

172
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,233
So I promise...

173
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:33,633
I'll really do my best.

174
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,167
But...

175
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:37,900
What?

176
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,600
You can't escape me.

177
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,067
You still need to take
your maintenance.

178
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:45,667
I thought...

179
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:48,833
I can get away with it.

180
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:58,267
There you go.

181
00:11:58,400 --> 00:11:58,933
I finished it.

182
00:11:59,067 --> 00:11:59,867
Yes.

183
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,133
We really need to stick
to the schedule.

184
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:05,667
By the way, what time is it?
I have to go.

185
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,000
Okay, I'll leave you for now.

186
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,133
Okay, Dad, be careful.

187
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:09,967
Okay.

188
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:19,333
Good morning!

189
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:21,933
Good morning, Sir.

190
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:22,800
Please sit down.

191
00:12:28,267 --> 00:12:32,733
Sir, with Markus' death, will
our case against Amo weaken?

192
00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:34,233
Not at all, Enriquez,

193
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:37,800
because we have a lot
of evidence against Amo.

194
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:42,633
Chief, isn't the guy who killed
Markus a hired killer?

195
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:44,433
We'll investigate on that,
Conde.

196
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:48,500
But for now, we need to focus

197
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,400
on the other problems
that Calabari will face.

198
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:54,933
We can't be distracted
by what happened.

199
00:12:56,867 --> 00:13:00,600
What do you think our next case
will be?

200
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,300
What is she doing?

201
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:44,933
Miss?

202
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:45,967
Miss...

203
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,067
Wake up, Miss.

204
00:13:53,967 --> 00:13:54,900
Help!

205
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,233
Help!

206
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,700
We didn't get an ID
from the victim,

207
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,467
so she's still Jane Doe.

208
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:10,533
She is between 18
and 20 years old.

209
00:14:18,767 --> 00:14:19,933
Look at this, Enriquez.

210
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:22,900
She has it on her arm...

211
00:14:24,033 --> 00:14:25,167
and on her leg.

212
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,433
Sir, by the looks of it,

213
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,500
it seems like she was carried
the way they do with pigs.

214
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:33,167
Was she raped, Doc?

215
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:35,100
The result was negative,
Lieutenant Conde.

216
00:14:35,367 --> 00:14:36,567
How about drugs, Doc?

217
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,067
I can't say yet because our drug
testing machine here is limited,

218
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,700
but it's possible.

219
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:46,400
Doc, what's that stuck
on her face?

220
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:49,400
Sir, that's a pimple patch.

221
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:51,533
That's trendy now,
especially among young people.

222
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:53,533
They use that to cover up
their pimples.

223
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,900
We need Doc Cecilia's help.

224
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:19,533
Shai!

225
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:21,933
Shai, my child!

226
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:30,533
Shai!

227
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:38,967
Shai...

228
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:53,900
Good day, Mrs. Reyes.

229
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:55,033
Sir...

230
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,000
I am Lieutenant Antonio Conde.

231
00:15:57,133 --> 00:16:00,333
This is Sergeant Enriquez.

232
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:05,700
Sir, Ma'am, can you find
the killer of my only child?

233
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:08,100
Please help me.

234
00:16:10,267 --> 00:16:11,567
Our condolences.

235
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,167
That's why we're here.

236
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,700
We will find the killer
of your child.

237
00:16:21,033 --> 00:16:23,267
Help me.

238
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:26,667
If it's okay with you,
we just have a few questions.

239
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:30,267
Okay, okay. It's okay.

240
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,100
When did you last see Shaira?

241
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:34,933
Two days ago.

242
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:39,133
She said she was going
to her classmate's place

243
00:16:39,267 --> 00:16:41,167
to work on a project.

244
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:45,300
I just found out this morning

245
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:48,733
that she didn't go
to her classmate's place.

246
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:56,933
Do you have any idea
where she went?

247
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:04,733
Sir, why did that happen?

248
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:09,033
Why did it have to happen
to my daughter?

249
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:11,667
My daughter is so kind.

250
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:18,400
If that hadn't happened
to my daughter,

251
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:23,100
she would have graduated by now.

252
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:25,833
I worked hard for my daughter,
Sir.

253
00:17:25,967 --> 00:17:29,267
I worked hard
just to provide for her,

254
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:32,167
and that's what ends up
happening to her?

255
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:37,100
Help me, Sir.

256
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,733
Excuse me, Mrs. Reyes.
The doctor is asking for you.

257
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,767
Sir, I've lost my mother.

258
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:07,767
I can't imagine how painful
it must be to lose a child.

259
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,667
That's why we're here,
Enriquez...

260
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:18,000
to help Mrs. Reyes get justice
for her daughter.

261
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,567
According to Mrs. Reyes,

262
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:23,133
her daughter seems very
different at home

263
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,733
compared to how she is outside.

264
00:18:26,367 --> 00:18:27,900
Where do we start, Sir?

265
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:31,200
We need to check if there's
a CCTV in the area

266
00:18:31,333 --> 00:18:32,900
where Shaira was seen.

267
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:35,400
Okay, Sir.

268
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:40,933
Lieutenant, I'm very sorry,
but...

269
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:44,900
the area where the woman
was found

270
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:46,233
is a blind spot
in our CCTV coverage.

271
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:50,500
That's why we didn't catch
how the victim ended up there.

272
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:52,467
Yes, Sir.

273
00:19:05,367 --> 00:19:06,067
Sir...

274
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:09,100
- isn't this area a blind spot?
- What?

275
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:10,467
There's an ATM here.

276
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,867
Don't ATMs have built-in CCTV?

277
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,400
You're right.

278
00:19:16,667 --> 00:19:17,867
Good job, Enriquez.

279
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:19,833
We need to get a copy
from the bank.

280
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,133
- Yes, Sir.
- Let's go.

281
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:22,800
- Thank you, Sir.
- Thank you.

282
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:24,067
- Thank you, Sir.
- You're welcome.

283
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,600
- You're welcome.
- We'll go ahead.

284
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,933
Garcia, what's your assignment
today?

285
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:39,433
Sir, I took the initiative
to oversee Jane Doe's autopsy.

286
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:41,400
Wait a minute...

287
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:46,133
that's Conde's case,
why are you meddling?

288
00:19:47,367 --> 00:19:49,600
Sir, because I'm helpful.

289
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,933
You're really something else,
Garcia.

290
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:55,133
You just want to see
Doc Cecilia.

291
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,133
Chief,

292
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,800
maybe you can stop interfering
in my love life for now?

293
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:03,333
Don't worry...

294
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:05,467
you'll be the principal sponsor
at our wedding.

295
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,667
- I'll go ahead, Godfather.
- Oh no.

296
00:20:09,067 --> 00:20:09,833
Go ahead.

297
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,600
I'll just go to the laboratory
of my love.

298
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:20,300
Conde, Enriquez.

299
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:21,433
Sir.

300
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:24,733
What's the update on Jane Doe?

301
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,633
She's been identified, Sir.

302
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:28,500
She's Shaira Reyes,

303
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:30,967
19 years old
from Barangay Sta. Elena.

304
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,767
We also got a copy
of the ATM's CCTV footage

305
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,167
from the bank, Sir.

306
00:20:35,467 --> 00:20:38,367
Sir, I hope we can find
something here,

307
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,100
so we can find out what happened
to Shaira.

308
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,800
Okay, let me know.

309
00:20:43,933 --> 00:20:44,800
Yes, Sir.

310
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:55,233
Enriquez, what time was Shaira
last seen outside?

311
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:57,967
It was about four
in the morning, Sir.

312
00:20:58,867 --> 00:20:59,533
Let me see.

313
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:14,300
There you go.

314
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,333
You can see the car's
license plate number.

315
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:19,267
You're right, Sir.

316
00:21:20,267 --> 00:21:24,800
Enriquez, call your contact.
We need to find this car.

317
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:25,533
Yes, Sir.

318
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:05,333
This is it, Sir.

319
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:10,667
Sir, do you think we can get any
information from this person?

320
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,033
I'm not sure.

321
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:14,867
But I hope they cooperate.

322
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:17,367
Okay, go and see them.

323
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:19,967
Why only me, Sir?

324
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,733
Well, based on experience,

325
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:25,333
when they see a police officer,
they run away.

326
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:28,933
So it's better for me
to stay here, just in case.

327
00:22:29,467 --> 00:22:31,900
Just admit that you're lazy

328
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:33,633
that's why you want me
to be in charge.

329
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,567
You can be honest.

330
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:37,367
Just tell me, it's okay with me.

331
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,233
Just in case, just in case.

332
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:44,600
He's already old.

333
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,300
He can't walk very far.

334
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,667
He has arthritis.

335
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:55,900
Anybody home?

336
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:58,600
Anybody home?

337
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:03,300
Good day.

338
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:08,033
I was just going to ask
if the car outside is yours?

339
00:23:10,267 --> 00:23:11,600
The car outside?

340
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:14,333
He did run away!

341
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,033
You're going to run away?

342
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:20,233
- Sorry, Sir.
- You want to have a hard time?

343
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,800
I told you, Enriquez.

344
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:26,733
Just in case, right?

345
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:33,900
A fluke.

346
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:35,267
Sir...

347
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:36,467
What?

348
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:38,200
Nothing, Sir.

349
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,800
I said, let's bring him already.

350
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:44,400
Sir, we didn't want that
to happen!

351
00:23:45,167 --> 00:23:46,467
We didn't know

352
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,433
that the drugs would have
that effect on Shaira, Sir.

353
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:52,100
What you did to Shaira
was no joke.

354
00:23:52,867 --> 00:23:54,667
You let her overdose.

355
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,500
Then you abandoned her
until she died.

356
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:03,700
Better yet...

357
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:06,033
just cooperate with us.

358
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,767
Tell us everything you know,

359
00:24:08,467 --> 00:24:10,667
and we'll do everything we can
to help you.

360
00:24:11,967 --> 00:24:12,600
Bro...

361
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:17,300
if you don't speak up,
more lives will suffer.

362
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:21,900
So if you really regret
what you did to Shaira,

363
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:24,367
now is the time to make amends.

364
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:26,133
Yes, yes, Sir.

365
00:24:26,267 --> 00:24:28,600
Okay, I'll cooperate with you,
Sir.

366
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:34,767
Stop!

367
00:24:40,933 --> 00:24:43,267
A mix of acid and NBOMe.

368
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:46,933
It's like a level up of LSD,
so it's really potent.

369
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:49,767
Does that mean one pimple patch
can kill you?

370
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:50,867
Not really.

371
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,633
The problem is, it's very
accessible and cheap.

372
00:24:53,767 --> 00:24:55,600
There's a new drug spreading.

373
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:58,700
I don't want that
to enter our village.

374
00:24:58,833 --> 00:24:59,867
Hey!

375
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:03,467
Let's stop going to coffee shops
every weekend.

376
00:25:03,633 --> 00:25:05,300
This mission of yours
is important.

377
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:07,000
Who's going to be my partner,
Boss?

378
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:09,333
Corporal Wilbert Mariano
reporting for duty, Sir.

379
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:11,267
I hope you're here
to accept my offer.

380
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,667
Do you know Alicia Enriquez?
